def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)

    if key is not None:
        # Check if key is a valid column name for grouping
        if key in obj.columns:
            gpr = key
            index_level = None
            in_axis = True
            exclusions = [key]
        else:
            raise KeyError(key)
    else:
        # No key provided, group by default axis (columns)
        gpr = obj.columns
        index_level = None
        in_axis = True
        exclusions = list(obj.columns)

    # create the Grouping
    ping = Grouping(
        group_axis,
        gpr,
        obj=obj,
        name=group_axis.name,
        level=index_level,
        sort=sort,
        observed=observed,
        in_axis=in_axis,
    )

    # Prepare the BaseGrouper and return
    grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, [ping], sort=sort, mutated=mutated)
    return grouper, exclusions, obj
